Rating: 2
We were disappointed with this receipe, after reading the great reviews. I think the big problem was the canned tomatoes -- I used DelMonte fresh cut and they still tasted processed. Follow other readers' recommendations and use fresh tomatoes.

Rating: 3
I left out the bread (intentionally) and coriander(accidentally) for this recipe. I usually bag on the people that don't follow the recipe's as written, but I guess that just means I'm getting a little more confident in making unique adjustments. SUCH AS...I used a mixture of canned and fresh red vine tomatoes. I used fresh filet of sole. Also instead of flouring and cooking the fish in a skillet, I baked it. I greased a dish, put in the filets, put a little salt and pepper and poured a little melted butter over the filet. I then topped the fish with the entire tomato mixture(reserving the liquid from earlier) I baked it at 450 degrees for "around" 15 minutes. I followed the rest of the recipe for the sauce and orange juice and put it over the fish. It was delicious. I also roasted some sliced zuchini with the remaining chopped shallots, olive oil, white wine, white wine vinegar, and salt and pepper. Yummy.

