What a disappointment. With all of the 4 fork reviews I thought this would be a winner. However, this recipe was so bland. I wasted 8 pieces of beautiful sea bass. Bruschetta should be saved for appetizers!

Rating: 4
Delicious! This is good even without the bread. I've served it with mashed potatoes, couscous, or rice, depending on the season and on my mood.

Rating: 4
This turned out fantastic! I used fresh tomatos (seeded and peeled) in place of the canned. I had quite a bit too much tomato mixture for the bruschetta, so i threw the extra into the 'sauce'. Served this with roasted butternut squash w/balsamic vinegar and broccoli rabe w/garlic & romano cheese... it was a beautiful, colourful presentation (and totally delicious).

Rating: 3
For a very cold winter night, I substituted mashed potato for the bread. I browned the potato, and treated it just as you would the bread. It was piping hot and filling and delicious!

Rating: 4
I love this recipe! I added some red pepper flakes to spice it up a bit, but it's wonderful as is! Make sure you put the tomato mixture on the toasted bread JUST before serving, to prevent any sogginess.

Rating: 4
Simply delicious. When time is scarce, it can be put together using store-bought bruschetta with excellent results.